1
00:01:23,830 --> 00:01:30,060
[Sunshine of My Life]

2
00:01:30,060 --> 00:01:32,940
[Episode 29]

3
00:01:40,220 --> 00:01:42,330
I won.

4
00:01:42,330 --> 00:01:45,680
You really haven't improved since you were little.

5
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:47,820
Big Brother, can't you just let me win once?

6
00:01:47,820 --> 00:01:50,290
You are playing the wrong moves. How can I let you win?

7
00:01:50,290 --> 00:01:52,910
You girls are really...

8
00:01:54,330 --> 00:01:57,280
We girls?

9
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:59,640
Who else?

10
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:02,400
It's so late. You need to rest.

11
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:04,390
I have to go.

12
00:02:05,420 --> 00:02:08,330
Brother, don't change the subject.

13
00:02:08,330 --> 00:02:10,480
Are you dating?

14
00:02:10,480 --> 00:02:12,860
Who told you I was?

15
00:02:12,860 --> 00:02:15,490
You said it.

16
00:02:15,490 --> 00:02:18,810
Did I? Why don't I remember?

17
00:02:18,810 --> 00:02:21,550
You're obviously having a guilty conscience.

18
00:02:21,550 --> 00:02:23,820
Is it the girl in the drawing?

19
00:02:23,820 --> 00:02:25,410
Tell me about her!

20
00:02:25,410 --> 00:02:28,930
You clearly have a girlfriend! Why don't you bring her to see me?

21
00:02:29,810 --> 00:02:34,530
She... probably will never forgive me.

22
00:02:36,460 --> 00:02:38,710
Why?

23
00:02:38,710 --> 00:02:40,360
Why wouldn't she forgive you?

24
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:43,140
Nothing. She has a boyfriend.

25
00:02:43,140 --> 00:02:46,320
Go to bed. Rest well and don't catch a cold. I'm leaving.

26
00:02:46,320 --> 00:02:50,230
Brother, I want orange juice.

27
00:02:50,230 --> 00:02:52,570
What are you doing drinking orange juice in the middle of the night?

28
00:02:52,570 --> 00:02:54,540
I just want to.

29
00:02:54,540 --> 00:02:56,300
You are so random.

30
00:02:56,300 --> 00:02:58,500
Buy it for me.

31
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:03,030
All right. Behave and wait for me.

32
00:03:14,610 --> 00:03:17,900
Do you remember if Qianqian stays in room 316 or B-318?

33
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:20,440
Let me ask.

34
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:23,940
Excuse me. Which room is Fang Qian in?

35
00:03:23,940 --> 00:03:25,780
In 318, over there.

36
00:03:25,780 --> 00:03:27,430
Thanks.

37
00:03:55,910 --> 00:03:57,800
Dad!

38
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:06,800
Dad, what are you doing in Shanghai?

39
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:09,660
Dad!

40
00:04:15,300 --> 00:04:19,510
I... I finally get to see you.

41
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:21,960
You scared me so much.

42
00:04:21,960 --> 00:04:24,420
- I'm so sorry.
- I thought...

43
00:04:24,420 --> 00:04:26,290
I thought you were dead.

44
00:04:26,290 --> 00:04:28,790
I'm sorry.

45
00:04:28,790 --> 00:04:32,130
Where were you? You didn't call home at all.

46
00:04:32,130 --> 00:04:34,610
I'm sorry, Dad.

47
00:04:34,610 --> 00:04:37,950
I was a liaison for World Without Borders.

48
00:04:37,950 --> 00:04:41,430
We didn't have any communication facility over there.

49
00:04:41,430 --> 00:04:44,280
I wasn't avoiding you on purpose.

50
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:46,940
You haven't told me what you are doing in Shanghai.

51
00:04:46,940 --> 00:04:49,630
I flew here as soon as I got the news.

52
00:04:49,630 --> 00:04:51,550
Are you in pain?

53
00:04:51,550 --> 00:04:53,170
- Do you feel uncomfortable?
- Sit, sit.

54
00:04:53,170 --> 00:04:56,660
Tell me if you are in pain? Are you feeling uncomfortable?

55
00:04:56,660 --> 00:04:59,370
I'm not in pain at all. You sit.

56
00:04:59,370 --> 00:05:01,510
They said you were sick.

57
00:05:01,510 --> 00:05:04,940
How are you feeling sick? Tell me.

58
00:05:04,940 --> 00:05:08,070
I'm not. I'm fine.

59
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:12,210
Have you been taking care of yourself?

60
00:05:12,210 --> 00:05:14,650
Your blood pressure is always high.

61
00:05:15,660 --> 00:05:18,770
You haven't told me. Where are you in pain?

62
00:05:18,770 --> 00:05:21,700
I know how to take blood pressure, Dad.

63
00:05:23,220 --> 00:05:27,700
Here. You came here in a hurry. Your blood pressure must be high.

64
00:05:27,700 --> 00:05:29,760
Don't move.

65
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:36,650
They say daughters care the most.

66
00:05:36,650 --> 00:05:40,350
Qian Qian is sick, but she still worries about you.

67
00:05:42,110 --> 00:05:44,020
Relax.

68
00:05:44,590 --> 00:05:47,090
Don't move. Don't move.

69
00:05:47,090 --> 00:05:48,960
All right.

70
00:05:57,870 --> 00:06:00,310
Don't move.

71
00:06:00,310 --> 00:06:04,400
Look! You are not taking care of yourself.

72
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:07,850
- You promised me!
- I'm fine. I'm fine.

73
00:06:07,850 --> 00:06:10,150
But you... you...

74
00:06:11,810 --> 00:06:13,860
I'm all fine when I saw you.

75
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:17,520
I'm sorry.

76
00:06:18,940 --> 00:06:21,800
I'm all good with you here. I'm glad you're back.

77
00:06:24,570 --> 00:06:28,370
Braised beef noodles, tomatoes, and orange juice. Are sure you don't want anything else?

78
00:06:28,370 --> 00:06:29,990
That's it.

79
00:06:39,330 --> 00:06:41,610
- Sis, also bring me a small bag of chips!
- Why are you here?

80
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:43,510
- Answer him.
- Okay!

81
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:45,880
What are you doing here?

82
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:48,410
I can't sleep so I came to see you.

83
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:53,570
I'm going to the market. How about coming with me?

84
00:07:04,250 --> 00:07:07,130
It's because we're like that we can walk like this.

85
00:07:07,130 --> 00:07:09,580
But if it's the same, then it's weird.

86
00:07:11,170 --> 00:07:13,200
As long as you like it.

87
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:17,280
Your little brother is so immature.

88
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:19,890
It's so late at night, yet he lets you go out alone to buy stuff.

89
00:07:19,890 --> 00:07:22,680
Because it's my shift tonight.

90
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:25,720
- What shift?
- In my family, we have shifts

91
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:28,260
for doing housework. It's my shift today.

92
00:07:28,260 --> 00:07:31,140
Ever since I was little, my mom would never

93
00:07:31,140 --> 00:07:33,130
take care of me more just because I'm a girl.

94
00:07:33,130 --> 00:07:36,260
She doesn't take care of my brother more just because he is younger.

95
00:07:36,260 --> 00:07:37,700
Your mother is so wise.

96
00:07:37,700 --> 00:07:39,550
In my family, my little cousin,

97
00:07:39,550 --> 00:07:41,890
because she's a girl and younger than me,

98
00:07:41,890 --> 00:07:43,550
she's undisciplined

99
00:07:43,550 --> 00:07:46,010
and out of control at home.

100
00:07:46,010 --> 00:07:48,090
So since you were little,

101
00:07:48,090 --> 00:07:50,640
you never sided with her more, right?

102
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:52,870
That's why she isn't very close to me.

103
00:07:52,870 --> 00:07:56,100
She likes Fang Xiaoyu more.

104
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:58,520
He spoils her a lot.

105
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:02,690
Didn't we agree to

106
00:08:02,690 --> 00:08:04,660
not mention him?

107
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:10,000
Time passes so fast.

108
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:13,940
Vacation is halfway done in a blink of an eye.

109
00:08:13,940 --> 00:08:17,350
- You haven't decided when you are going back?
- Not yet.

110
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:23,750
But why aren't you even a little bit sad?

111
00:08:29,220 --> 00:08:31,110
Why should I be sad?

112
00:08:31,110 --> 00:08:32,870
Because...

113
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:37,310
If everything goes well,

114
00:08:37,310 --> 00:08:40,230
I can go visit you in France often.

115
00:08:40,230 --> 00:08:42,550
- Really?
- Of course.

116
00:08:42,550 --> 00:08:44,390
Is there hope for the acquisition?

117
00:08:44,390 --> 00:08:48,160
The future is bright. Miya agreed

118
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:51,370
to come to Shanghai for our Symphony of Clouds and Mist press conference.

119
00:08:52,630 --> 00:08:54,030
That's great!

120
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:57,640
Is there anything I can help with?

121
00:08:59,070 --> 00:09:02,750
As a good designer, you need to use your talent.

122
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:05,490
But as my girlfriend,

123
00:09:06,260 --> 00:09:09,000
you can help me

124
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:11,240
in many ways.

125
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:14,510
What are you thinking?

126
00:09:14,510 --> 00:09:16,340
- You don't understand?
- I don't know. I don't understand.

127
00:09:16,340 --> 00:09:19,260
- I don't know what you are talking about.
- Don't you?

128
00:09:19,260 --> 00:09:21,570
Should I do

129
00:09:21,570 --> 00:09:24,280
a Chinese cuisine theme design?

130
00:09:24,280 --> 00:09:26,880
I could use Xiao Long Bao to design the wedding dress.

131
00:09:29,070 --> 00:09:31,070
Duoduo wouldn't want to wear it.

132
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:36,130
Think about it. If Duoduo wears a Xiao Long Bao wedding dress,

133
00:09:36,130 --> 00:09:38,310
wouldn't that be interesting?

134
00:09:38,310 --> 00:09:42,470
That is interesting, but you wouldn't find a wife in this lifetime.

135
00:09:43,510 --> 00:09:45,640
You women don't understand a guy's romance.

136
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:49,040
Men don't understand women's hearts.

137
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:51,310
Xiao Long Bao wedding gown.

138
00:09:51,310 --> 00:09:53,530
I'm going to Suzhou this afternoon.

139
00:09:53,530 --> 00:09:55,540
This afternoon?

140
00:09:55,540 --> 00:09:57,360
Don't forget to confirm the draft.

141
00:09:57,360 --> 00:10:00,110
Then, discuss it well with the embroiderers.

142
00:10:51,670 --> 00:10:53,690
Thank you.

143
00:10:53,690 --> 00:10:55,040
For what?

144
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:57,990
If it weren't for you, I would be soaked.

145
00:11:01,010 --> 00:11:03,570
Yes, that's right.

146
00:11:10,170 --> 00:11:12,040
- Are you going to Suzhou?
- Yes.

147
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:13,940
To do what?

148
00:11:13,940 --> 00:11:18,160
Going to the building site and to visit your master.

149
00:11:18,160 --> 00:11:21,340
- What about you?
- I am also going to see my master.

150
00:11:21,340 --> 00:11:24,850
I feel like Water Color is lacking a little charm.

151
00:11:24,850 --> 00:11:27,020
I need to discuss it with her.

152
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:31,020
Of course, if time allows, I can collect local materials.

153
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:36,530
What do you think the Water Colors lack?

154
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:41,400
I think it needs something to grab people's attention.

155
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:44,360
And... a sense of movement.

156
00:11:44,360 --> 00:11:47,360
So you want to substitute it with Su Embroidery.

157
00:11:49,630 --> 00:11:51,360
You've worked hard.

158
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:54,030
You don't even get a break on weekends.

159
00:11:54,030 --> 00:11:56,210
I'm fine.

160
00:12:04,540 --> 00:12:07,640
- Your hair is wet. Let me dry it for you.
- I'll do it myself.

161
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:09,620
- Let me do it.
- Okay.

162
00:12:16,060 --> 00:12:18,760
Give me your glasses.

163
00:12:19,980 --> 00:12:23,020
- I'll give you my eyes.
- Your glasses.
(T/N: Eyes and glasses have a similar pronunciation)

164
00:12:23,020 --> 00:12:25,210
You have my eyes already.

165
00:12:26,010 --> 00:12:32,260
♫ I want to give you the world's gentlest understanding ♫

166
00:12:32,260 --> 00:12:34,530
Your little bun.

167
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:41,140
I don't have an eyeglass cloth, just a tissue.

168
00:12:41,140 --> 00:12:43,520
- As long as it works.
- All right.

169
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:46,760
I will make it clean. Very clean.

170
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:53,900
♫ That I'm the inexhaustible candlelight to your endless night ♫

171
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:57,270
♫ You're the one I love extremely ♫

172
00:12:57,270 --> 00:13:00,090
♫ You're a sweet and sour piece of candy ♫

173
00:13:00,090 --> 00:13:04,260
Try it on.

174
00:13:04,260 --> 00:13:07,970
♫ I really want to see your smile ♫

175
00:13:07,970 --> 00:13:10,790
♫ Many people come and go ♫

176
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:12,950
What's this for?

177
00:13:12,950 --> 00:13:14,680
Being cute...

178
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:19,070
Aren't you always?

179
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:22,780
Have some water.

180
00:13:22,780 --> 00:13:24,580
Thank you.

181
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:34,430
All right, got it.

182
00:13:37,190 --> 00:13:44,130
♫ I want to give you the world's gentlest understanding ♫

183
00:13:45,060 --> 00:13:46,770
Let's go.

184
00:13:46,770 --> 00:13:50,420
♫ When you feel tired, I'll be your softest pillow ♫

185
00:13:50,420 --> 00:13:53,850
♫ I want… ♫

186
00:13:53,850 --> 00:13:57,300
♫ you to personally tell me you love me, too ♫

187
00:13:57,300 --> 00:14:01,270
♫ That I'm the inexhaustible candlelight to your endless night ♫

188
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:06,270
How long are you staying this time?

189
00:14:06,270 --> 00:14:10,410
Not very long. I need to get back to school when the school break is over.

190
00:14:11,180 --> 00:14:13,000
You've lost some weight.

191
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:15,420
Did you study too hard?

192
00:14:15,420 --> 00:14:19,770
Master, I gained so much weight that my face is round.

193
00:14:19,770 --> 00:14:22,660
No matter how skinny you are,

194
00:14:22,660 --> 00:14:25,020
you always say you've gained weight.

195
00:14:25,020 --> 00:14:27,450
Are you used to eating French cuisine?

196
00:14:27,450 --> 00:14:30,690
I can cook for myself, Master. Don't you know?

197
00:14:30,690 --> 00:14:32,630
I know.

198
00:14:32,630 --> 00:14:35,150
I know you're capable.

199
00:14:35,150 --> 00:14:40,040
Of course, after all, whose student am I?

200
00:14:41,510 --> 00:14:44,470
My student always comes with honey in her mouth.

201
00:14:44,470 --> 00:14:46,400
I know.

202
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:49,130
Do you know that I once enjoyed the limelight?

203
00:14:49,130 --> 00:14:52,210
- thanks to Su Embroidery.
- Really?

204
00:14:52,210 --> 00:14:54,520
Those foreign designers

205
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:57,340
like many kinds of our Chinese embroidery so very much.

206
00:14:57,340 --> 00:15:00,040
- They like it a lot!
- Of course.

207
00:15:00,040 --> 00:15:03,070
Our ancestor's treasure passed on generation after generation

208
00:15:03,070 --> 00:15:05,570
is the greatest.

209
00:15:14,310 --> 00:15:16,670
Master, is it these two colors?

210
00:15:16,670 --> 00:15:18,620
Yes.

211
00:15:18,620 --> 00:15:21,990
[Fragrant Lotus Pavillion]

212
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:33,000
One more thread here.

213
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:45,650
Master, let me pour you some tea.

214
00:15:52,910 --> 00:15:55,840
- Please have some tea.
- Thank you.

215
00:15:59,390 --> 00:16:03,500
I'm here for your advice

216
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:07,970
on how to use such a great thing better.

217
00:16:10,650 --> 00:16:13,070
You just said you are here for me.

218
00:16:13,070 --> 00:16:15,800
It's for President Tang's company.

219
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:19,300
You know that I'm a temporary assistant in his company.

220
00:16:19,300 --> 00:16:22,990
I still have some tiny issues with my work.

221
00:16:22,990 --> 00:16:26,070
What issues? Let's talk about it.

222
00:16:26,070 --> 00:16:29,120
Water Color is the new theme for Songtang's show this time.

223
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:33,910
I'm planning on using Su Embroidery to make some pendants to decorate the clothes.

224
00:16:33,910 --> 00:16:35,790
My current idea is

225
00:16:35,790 --> 00:16:40,770
other than the belt and the decoration, the whole piece is plain colored.

226
00:16:41,790 --> 00:16:45,670
So you don't know where to start, right?

227
00:16:45,670 --> 00:16:48,810
I've looked at many patterns.

228
00:16:48,810 --> 00:16:50,940
Those flowers and such are too cliche.

229
00:16:50,940 --> 00:16:53,890
The zodiac animals don't fit.

230
00:16:53,890 --> 00:16:56,400
Happiness, position, and longevity look too old-fashioned.

231
00:16:56,400 --> 00:17:00,090
What do you think of koi fish?

232
00:17:00,090 --> 00:17:01,910
Koi fish?

233
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:05,150
That's a good one.

234
00:17:05,150 --> 00:17:09,120
Don't you young people like to repost koi fish pictures for good luck?

235
00:17:09,120 --> 00:17:11,240
This is a good idea.

236
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:14,010
But even though fish are not a hard pattern,

237
00:17:14,010 --> 00:17:18,090
but it's still hard to make it vivid.

238
00:17:18,970 --> 00:17:21,330
That's true.

239
00:17:22,220 --> 00:17:24,060
But...

240
00:17:24,760 --> 00:17:27,950
you could use the Kelin stitch method.

241
00:17:27,950 --> 00:17:31,810
First, make a horizontal stitch based on the breadth of the scale,

242
00:17:31,810 --> 00:17:36,890
then use a short needle to stitch a small triangle on it.

243
00:17:36,890 --> 00:17:40,860
And then, use two equal-length short stitches

244
00:17:40,860 --> 00:17:43,090
to close the scale.

245
00:17:44,250 --> 00:17:46,720
About the fish's eyes...

246
00:17:48,180 --> 00:17:50,380
Use the knot stitch.

247
00:17:50,380 --> 00:17:53,360
It would look more three-dimensional.

248
00:17:53,360 --> 00:17:56,520
For the decorative water plants, you could use the backstitch.

249
00:17:56,520 --> 00:17:59,720
This way, the angles can be hidden away

250
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:02,320
and can be enlarged at will.

251
00:18:04,060 --> 00:18:06,270
You are so amazing.

252
00:18:06,270 --> 00:18:09,050
You directly enlightened the person lost in dreams.

253
00:18:09,050 --> 00:18:11,920
This way, the scales of the fish will be shiny

254
00:18:11,920 --> 00:18:13,750
and will reflect the light.

255
00:18:13,750 --> 00:18:16,350
Thank you. I will try it right away.

256
00:18:16,350 --> 00:18:19,550
Okay. Go try it.

257
00:18:19,550 --> 00:18:22,290
Right, another thing.

258
00:18:22,290 --> 00:18:24,280
Go ahead.

259
00:18:24,280 --> 00:18:26,730
President Tang is waiting for you in the office.

260
00:18:26,730 --> 00:18:29,930
President Tang? Why didn't you say it earlier?

261
00:18:29,930 --> 00:18:32,570
I wanted to talk to you more.

262
00:18:32,570 --> 00:18:34,610
Let's go.

263
00:18:39,690 --> 00:18:41,630
When it comes to embroidery,

264
00:18:41,630 --> 00:18:44,150
you can just call me in the future.

