- Let's see them.

278
00:19:28,190 --> 00:19:29,770
It's so pretty.

279
00:19:29,770 --> 00:19:34,360
I was afraid the fluidity Director Xia wants would be hard to achieve.

280
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:36,890
It did take a lot of effort.

281
00:19:36,890 --> 00:19:39,310
We used some light-colored threads

282
00:19:39,310 --> 00:19:43,740
to mix with the dark-colored threads to achieve this shine.

283
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:54,130
This is something. Thank you for your hard work.

284
00:19:54,130 --> 00:19:55,730
You are so kind.

285
00:19:55,730 --> 00:19:58,570
This is my favorite thing to do.

286
00:19:58,570 --> 00:20:00,680
No matter what happens next,

287
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:03,580
tell me first thing, and I will take care of it.

288
00:20:03,580 --> 00:20:05,400
Thank you.

289
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:15,270
You are sweating again.

290
00:20:15,270 --> 00:20:17,770
My teacher is here.

291
00:20:18,380 --> 00:20:20,430
Your master experienced it. What are you afraid of?

292
00:20:20,430 --> 00:20:23,490
It's so embarrassing.

293
00:20:23,490 --> 00:20:25,980
Shall we see the next one?

294
00:20:33,590 --> 00:20:36,460
I will put some comfortable chairs inside that gazebo.

295
00:20:36,460 --> 00:20:38,520
When the embroiderers are tired,
[Guest Pavillion]

296
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:41,310
they can rest there.

297
00:20:44,060 --> 00:20:48,200
Also, I'm thinking about building three exhibit rooms here.

298
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:51,260
One of them is Master Li's own show.

299
00:20:51,260 --> 00:20:56,010
One of them will have the Su Embroidery pieces she collected.

300
00:20:56,010 --> 00:20:59,180
The last one will be

301
00:20:59,970 --> 00:21:02,160
your Master Li's classroom.

302
00:21:06,040 --> 00:21:08,520
Is there anything missing?

303
00:21:08,520 --> 00:21:11,060
I think...

304
00:21:11,060 --> 00:21:13,330
you are too thorough.

305
00:21:13,330 --> 00:21:16,360
Don't you feel happy?

306
00:21:18,620 --> 00:21:20,490
It's fine.

307
00:21:20,490 --> 00:21:24,470
- Why are you never satisfied?
- You are poking me again!

308
00:21:27,310 --> 00:21:29,350
Thank you.

309
00:21:29,350 --> 00:21:31,570
What for?

310
00:21:31,570 --> 00:21:34,150
Right! How's the material collecting? Want me to come with you?

311
00:21:34,150 --> 00:21:36,060
Aren't you here to supervise the construction?

312
00:21:36,060 --> 00:21:40,290
The Symphony of Clouds and Mist is one of the most important projects of the company and you're one of the designers.

313
00:21:40,290 --> 00:21:43,590
Collecting materials with you is part of my job.

314
00:21:43,590 --> 00:21:47,080
Also, I am here to supervise you.

315
00:21:47,570 --> 00:21:51,100
Being supervised by you can't be good.

316
00:21:51,690 --> 00:21:54,330
It's also very romantic.

317
00:22:28,350 --> 00:22:31,350
I've been keeping you company for a while. Did you find any inspiration?

318
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:38,150
Are you just slacking off and trying to go on a date with me?

319
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:41,880
You've been keeping me company for this long and didn't say you are tired.

320
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:44,950
Are you trying to get me to treat you and eat crab?

321
00:22:44,950 --> 00:22:46,820
Then, are you inviting me or not?

322
00:22:46,820 --> 00:22:49,010
Depends on how you do.

323
00:22:49,010 --> 00:22:51,190
What should I do?

324
00:22:51,830 --> 00:22:55,020
You need to figure it out yourself.

325
00:23:00,630 --> 00:23:05,280
Inspiration is not something that just shows up.

326
00:23:08,350 --> 00:23:12,390
Creativity is challenging oneself.

327
00:23:12,390 --> 00:23:15,510
Once you are in the process, you can never be completely satisfied.

328
00:23:15,510 --> 00:23:20,110
Even if you do, it's all temporary.

329
00:23:20,110 --> 00:23:23,690
What is the biggest problem you have right now?

330
00:23:24,320 --> 00:23:28,340
Water Color only has black and white

331
00:23:28,340 --> 00:23:31,020
as its main color, and then it has ink-splash

332
00:23:31,020 --> 00:23:33,160
to mix those two.

333
00:23:33,160 --> 00:23:38,160
But I just think it lacks elegance.

334
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:44,970
My instincts are telling me that white might be the problem,

335
00:23:45,650 --> 00:23:48,900
because white can be added to any piece.

336
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:53,150
For example, light feathers, white snow,

337
00:23:53,150 --> 00:23:56,080
and soft clouds. They all give the people

338
00:23:56,080 --> 00:23:58,610
a different sense of white.

339
00:23:59,530 --> 00:24:02,380
I remember there was once an intellectual,

340
00:24:02,380 --> 00:24:05,120
who said the character white of oracle inscriptions and bell-cauldron inscriptions

341
00:24:05,120 --> 00:24:09,780
is like the highest rising point of the sun.

342
00:24:12,930 --> 00:24:16,350
The reeds are flourishing, white dew turns into frost.

343
00:24:16,350 --> 00:24:20,490
The reeds and the frosted dew

344
00:24:20,490 --> 00:24:24,130
reflect the scenery of the water.

345
00:24:24,870 --> 00:24:27,710
The stream runs clearly, the white pebbles are spotless.

346
00:24:27,710 --> 00:24:32,040
The surging river water keeps splashing

347
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:36,020
and makes the color of the rocks become translucent.

348
00:24:38,250 --> 00:24:40,160
White...

349
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:42,230
is the color of light.

350
00:24:42,230 --> 00:24:45,350
It's power.

351
00:24:45,350 --> 00:24:49,290
It accumulates a lot and gives a little. It's the power of dripping water dripping to rock.

352
00:24:50,180 --> 00:24:54,350
Thank you for inspiring me.

353
00:24:54,350 --> 00:24:58,430
I finally know what Water Color lacks.

354
00:24:58,430 --> 00:25:02,190
Thank you! I need to make note of it.

355
00:25:04,730 --> 00:25:07,370
Are you just thanking me with words?

356
00:25:07,370 --> 00:25:09,360
Then...

357
00:25:09,360 --> 00:25:11,360
I will buy you crabs.

358
00:25:11,360 --> 00:25:13,600
I just had it last night.

359
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:16,850
What do you want then?

360
00:25:17,280 --> 00:25:20,450
Is there anything else you can thank me with?

361
00:25:20,450 --> 00:25:22,450
Like what?

362
00:25:24,550 --> 00:25:27,000
Let me think.

363
00:25:32,220 --> 00:25:34,630
I'm creating.

364
00:25:40,750 --> 00:25:43,630
I'm so tired of walking around with you.

365
00:25:44,760 --> 00:25:47,360
And there's no reward.

366
00:25:48,180 --> 00:25:50,220
It's so sad.

367
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:05,100
I'm sad.

368
00:26:08,060 --> 00:26:09,870
What are you doing?

369
00:26:12,310 --> 00:26:14,660
You're not even showing your appreciation a little.

370
00:26:40,220 --> 00:26:42,050
That's not enough.

371
00:26:44,420 --> 00:26:46,170
There are a lot of people.

372
00:26:46,170 --> 00:26:48,610
Come here. Let me tell you something.

